# ============================================================================
# Key Advantages of Relative Timing
# ============================================================================
#
# ✓ Easy to adjust spacing - change one offset, pattern adjusts
# ✓ Perfect for sequences and patterns
# ✓ Natural for delay/echo effects
# ✓ Works well for drum programming (tight groove control)
# ✓ Arpeggiator and strum effects
# ✓ Time-stretching patterns (change all offsets proportionally)
# ✓ Less mental math than calculating absolute positions
#
# When to Use Relative Timing:
# - Sequences where spacing matters more than position
# - Delay chains and echo effects
# - Drum grooves with specific feel
# - Arpeggiated patterns
# - Strum simulations
# - Swing/shuffle rhythms
#
# When NOT to Use:
# - Events that must happen at specific times (use absolute)
# - Events tied to song structure (use musical)
# - First event in a section (need reference point)
#
# ============================================================================

